					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There's plenty more than 200 #$FF's at the end of the SMW cartridge, but I guess they just didn't know how much memory they had left until they were done.
<br />
<br />A strategy I use, is during v-blank I usually have the accumulator in 8-bit mode, and index in 16-bit mode.  When I need to write to a single register I use the accumulator.  If I need to write to 2 back to back registers like $2116 &amp; $2117, I use X or Y.  That saves memory, development time and speed all at the same time.</div>

